-> Software / IDE
  1. Arduino IDE – for microcontroller programming
  2. TinkerCAD or Fritzing – for circuit simulation
  3. EasyEDA (or KiCad) – to generate Gerber files
  4. GitHub – for hosting the project
  5. OBS Studio / Mobile Camera – to record demo video

-> Hardware
 1. Arduino Uno (or equivalent microcontroller)
 2. 2x LDRs (Light Dependent Resistors) – to sense sunlight
 3. 2x 10kΩ resistors – for LDR voltage divider
 4. Servo Motor / DC Motor + Motor Driver – for panel movement
 5. Solar Panel (optional for physical prototype)
 6. Breadboard + jumper wires
 7. Power supply (Battery or USB)
